  1. What is the EPSG code of the Counties dataset? Is this a geographic or a projected coordinate reference system? (Or, does this CRS use angular or planar coordinate units?) To what datum is this CRS associated? (Tip: look the EPSG code on https://spatialreference.org)

ANSWER: The ESPG code for this dataset is 4269. EPSG stands for European Petroleum Survey Group and is an organization that maintains a geodetic parameter database with standard codes, the EPSG codes, for coordinate systems, datums, spheroids, units and such alike. Every geographic object (coordinate system, spheroid, unit etc.) gets assigned a unique number. CRS uses angular coordinate units. Common global datums for CRS are WGS84 and NAD83.
